          About the Job
                Data Scientist/Marketing Analyst
              Vision Group Holdings, with 120 Centers located in 41 States as well as Canada, is the world's largest provider of laser vision correction surgery operating under two major brands, The LASIK Vision Institute and TLC Laser Eye Centers.
              The LASIK Vision Institute is the country’s leading provider of LASIK laser vision correction. Built upon a commitment to provide better vision for a better value, LVI delivers enhanced vision and a superior, personalized patient experience at a highly accessible price point. At the LASIK Vision Institute®, our experienced independent LASIK eye surgeons have conducted over 1,000,000 procedures nationwide.
              TLC Laser Eye Centers is a longstanding leader in LASIK technology. Our exceptionally experienced surgeons, with the help of North America’s largest network of affiliated optometrists, aim to safely take away the limitations and inconvenience of glasses and contact lenses. More than 7,000 doctors have chosen TLC for their own laser vision correction procedures– the ultimate endorsement.
                Description:
               We are looking for someone who is passionate about understanding data, well versed in scalable data mining and machine learning techniques, and loves to build models.
               This role is a multidisciplinary blend of statistics, technology, and business strategy, all applied in tandem to discover key insights that lie hidden in our data sets.
               The ideal candidate will be able to understand business challenges, map analytical approaches and build models to derive actionable insights.
               Responsibilities:
               Meet with executive management to understand major business opportunities and challenges (likely areas include financial performance, customer satisfaction, demographics and local economics)
               Frame relevant issues, map out analytical approaches and gather data
               Design, build, and run complex analytic models that drive insights significant to the business
               Use business intelligence tools to communicate insights to executive management
                Qualifications:
               Familiarity with relational databases and SQL, data transformation (ETL), data mining, ad-hoc analysis
               Extensive experience with Python, R, Stata, SAS, SPSS, Matlab or another statistical language
               Deep knowledge of standard techniques (e.g., Logistic Regression, Cluster Analysis, Random Forests, Experimental Design)
               Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau)
               Experience working with real data either through a current job or through projects during graduate school
               Ability to learn things quickly and work independently
               An analytical, creative, and innovative approach to solving difficult problems
